The paper deals with the problem of representing and querying sorted integer sequences, which is a central problem in information retrieval (IR) and database systems (DB). Therefore, cs.IR and cs.DB are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also proposes a solution that involves partitioning and slicing the sequences, which is a data structure problem and falls under the category of data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the compression of inverted indices, which is a topic in compression (cs.CR). Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of the proposed solution, which involves analyzing the space/time trade-off, a topic in machine learning (cs.LG).
